Key Match Events: Lebanon defender Khalil Khamis accidentally kicked China's Dai Wai Tsun in the face during the 23rd minute of the match, leading to a VAR review but no punishment was given.
Post-Match Reflections: The match ended in a goalless draw, allowing group toppers and hosts Qatar to progress to the knockout stage while China's future hangs in the balance after failing to register a win in their first two group games.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Cedars will next face Tajikistan in their final group game on Monday while the Dragon's Team faces the mighty Qataris in a must-win clash on the same day.
